# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# Golden/oracle fixtures under tests/golden/ ARE committed, on purpose:
# the .nc rasters in tests/golden/*/out/ are the terra-generated oracles that
# test_landfills_golden.py and test_ng_transmission_golden.py compare against
# cell-for-cell, and the .csv/.geojson files are their pinned inputs. They are
# small (24 KB per raster) and regenerating them needs a working R + terra
# install, so do not add a `*.nc` / `*.tif` ignore rule here — it would silently
# strip the port's only correctness oracle.
#
# Shipped package data in src/m3t/data/ (parquet/json converted from the R
# .rda by _data_raw/build_data.py) IS committed so the package is installable.

# Downloaded archives, if a run or capture script ever caches one in-tree.
*.zip
